  "body": "It would be great to be able to inherit tasks, creating a new one that takes the definitions of the base class and adds new parameters or overrides something.\r\n\r\n\r\nLike this: \r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n  task(\"ens:baseTask\", \"Some task with some params\")\r\n    .addParam(\"param1\", \"Sample param 1\", types.address)\r\n    .addOptionalParam(\"param2\", \"Sample param 2\", undefined, types.boolean)\r\n    .setAction(actionFunction);\r\n\r\n  task(\"ens:otherTask\", \"Inherist from baseTask and redefines some params\", {inherits: \"ens:baseTask\"})\r\n    .addParam(\"param3\", \"Sample param 3\", types.address)\r\n    .addOptionalParam(\"param2\", \"Redefines Sample param 2\", undefined, types.boolean)\r\n    .setAction(actionFunction2);\r\n``` \r\n\r\nThis will help a lot when we need some new parameters to customize existing tasks or in general. ",
